observations.recommendation:
We recommended, and the Management agreed, that the Municipal Mayor require both the Municipal Accountant and the Acting Municipal Treasurer to:


reconcile the discrepancies totaling ₱607,570.79 between the amount withheld and the amount remitted for the current year;

reconcile and identify with the employees’ individual ledger cards the previous years’ outstanding balance of ₱2,095,109.69;

remit immediately the identified/reconciled balance of Due to GSIS, Pag-IBIG and PhilHealth accounts as at December 31, 2023; and

effect the necessary accounting entries based on the result of reconciliation.

We recommended and the Management agreed that the Municipal Mayor:

take full advantage of the utilization of available funds for disaster preparedness, prevention and mitigation in order to further enhance the capability of the Municipality to effectively and efficiently prevent losses and alleviate the impacts of disasters;

require the Municipal Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Officer to;

enhance the monitoring of LDRRMF utilization focusing on PPAs requiring the highest priority in terms of urgency and/or impact on the four thematic areas of DRRM; and

ensure efficient and effective implementation of all programmed projects identified during the budget year to optimize the utilization of the fund and to warrant that the goals and objectives of reducing disaster risk and enhancing disaster preparedness and response capabilities are achieved;

We recommend and the Management agreed, that the Municipal Mayor and the Municipal Human Resource Management Officer ensure that travel allowances are paid only to JO personnel whose contracts explicitly authorize to travel;
We further recommended and the Management agreed, that the Municipal Mayor issue an Executive Order establishing internal policies, guidelines, and limitations on travel claims for JO personnel; and
Lastly, we recommended and the Management agreed, that the Municipal Accountant thoroughly review the travel claims of JO personnel to ensure they are properly approved by the authorized official and supported by the required certifications and other necessary documents before processing payment.

We recommended and the Management agreed, that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to:
Reconcile the discrepancies totaling ₱946,085.30 between the amount withheld and the amount remitted for the current year;
Reconcile the previous years’ net outstanding balance of ₱2,156,896.52;
Remit immediately the identified/reconciled balance of Due to GSIS, Pag-IBIG, PhilHealth and GOCCs accounts as at December 31, 2024; and
Effect the necessary accounting entries based on the result of reconciliation.
